The paper deals with the use of sparsity-inducing regularizers during training of Convolution Neural Networks (CNNs) to reduce memory and runtime cost involved in deploying the learned CNNs. This makes it highly likely that the paper belongs to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with the optimization of deep neural networks, which makes it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of regularization techniques, which is a common topic in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on image datasets, which is a common topic in the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category.
